One of the museum’s surprises is the Gabriela Mistral Room. Inaugurated in 1983, it was created to preserve the legacy of the Chilean poet and diplomat. It holds personal objects that provide insight into her most intimate and spiritual side: national and international decorations, devotional items, and a replica of the Nobel Prize in Literature she received in 1945. Mistral bequeathed this award to the people of Chile, under the custody of the Franciscan Order. This room honors her as a key figure in Chilean and Latin American culture.



